# load the data
rse_brain <- readRDS("/Users/alessandrodiamanti/Downloads/rse_brain.RDS")
rse_liver <- readRDS("/Users/alessandrodiamanti/Downloads/rse_liver.RDS")
rse_lung <- readRDS("/Users/alessandrodiamanti/Downloads/rse_lung.RDS")

pre_processing<-length(rowData(rse_brain)$gbkey)

#for brain
#drop rRna genes
rse <- rse_brain[
  rowData(rse_brain)$gbkey != 'rRNA' &
    !is.na(rowData(rse_brain)$gbkey),]

# Drop reads mapped to Pseudogenes
rse <- rse[
  rowData(rse)$gbkey != 'Gene' &
    !is.na(rowData(rse)$gbkey),]

# Drop reads mapped to mitochondrial genes
rse <- rse[rowRanges(rse)@seqnames != "chrM", ]

# rese_brain now is free from unuseful rowws

rse_brain<-rse

# same for liver
rse <- rse_liver[
  rowData(rse_liver)$gbkey != 'rRNA' &
    !is.na(rowData(rse_liver)$gbkey),]

# Drop reads mapped to Pseudogenes
rse <- rse[
  rowData(rse)$gbkey != 'Gene' &
    !is.na(rowData(rse)$gbkey),]

# Drop reads mapped to mitochondrial genes
rse <- rse[rowRanges(rse)@seqnames != "chrM", ]

# rese_liver ora  il nuovo oggetto adeguatamente
#scremato

rse_liver<-rse

#and for lung 
rse <- rse_lung[
  rowData(rse_lung)$gbkey != 'rRNA' &
    !is.na(rowData(rse_lung)$gbkey),]

# Drop reads mapped to Pseudogenes
rse <- rse[
  rowData(rse)$gbkey != 'Gene' &
    !is.na(rowData(rse)$gbkey),]

# Drop reads mapped to mitochondrial genes
rse <- rse[rowRanges(rse)@seqnames != "chrM", ]

# rese_liver ora  il nuovo oggetto adeguatamente
#scremato

rse_lung<-rse

#transform data in the columns into counts

assays(rse_lung)$counts <- transform_counts(rse_lung)

#transform data in the columns into TPM

assays(rse_liver)$TPM <- getTPM(rse_liver)
assays(rse_lung)$TPM<- getTPM(rse_lung)

rse_brain_selected <- rse_brain[,c(30,38,40)]
rse_liver_selected <- rse_liver[,c(28,34,36)]
rse_lung_selected <- rse_lung[,c(27,30,31)]
counts_brain_selected <- assays(rse_brain_selected)$counts
counts_liver_selected <- assays(rse_liver_selected)$counts
counts_lung_selected <- assays(rse_lung_selected)$counts

x <- cbind(counts_brain_selected,counts_liver_selected,counts_lung_selected)

colnames(x) <- c("Brain30", "Brain38","Brain40","Liver28", "Liver34","Liver36","Lung27","Lung30","Lung31")

rownames(x) <- rowData(rse_brain_selected)$gene_name

y <- DGEList(counts=x)

group <- as.factor(c("Brain","Brain","Brain","Liver","Liver","Liver","Lung","Lung","Lung"))

y$samples$group <- group
# add annotation of the samples on the columns 
y$samples$rin <- as.factor(c(colData(rse_brain_selected)$gtex.smrin,colData(rse_liver_selected)$gtex.smrin,colData(rse_lung_selected)$gtex.smrin))

y$samples$slice <- as.factor(c(colData(rse_brain_selected)$gtex.smtsd,colData(rse_liver_selected)$gtex.smtsd,colData(rse_lung_selected)$gtex.smtsd))

y$samples$sex <- as.factor(c(colData(rse_brain_selected)$gtex.sex,colData(rse_liver_selected)$gtex.sex,colData(rse_lung_selected)$gtex.sex))

y$samples$age <- as.factor(c(colData(rse_brain_selected)$gtex.age,colData(rse_liver_selected)$gtex.age,colData(rse_lung_selected)$gtex.age))

y$samples$rRNA <- as.factor(c(colData(rse_brain_selected)$gtex.smrrnart,colData(rse_liver_selected)$gtex.smrrnart,colData(rse_lung_selected)$gtex.smrrnart))

y$samples$mapped <- as.factor(c(colData(rse_brain_selected)$"recount_qc.star.uniquely_mapped_reads_%_both", colData(rse_liver_selected)$"recount_qc.star.uniquely_mapped_reads_%_both",colData(rse_lung_selected)$"recount_qc.star.uniquely_mapped_reads_%_both"))

y$samples$chrm <- as.factor(c(colData(rse_brain_selected)$"recount_qc.aligned_reads%.chrm", colData(rse_liver_selected)$"recount_qc.aligned_reads%.chrm",colData(rse_lung_selected)$"recount_qc.aligned_reads%.chrm"))

# fitting the linear model with the data
fit <- glmQLFit(y, design)

# now let's see which genes are up-regulated  
#liver top, brain bottom
qlfLiB <- glmQLFTest(fit, contrast=c(-1,1,0))

#lung (top) vs brain (bottom)
qlfLuB <- glmQLFTest(fit, contrast=c(-1,0,1))
#lung (top) vs liver (bottom)
qlfLuLi <- glmQLFTest(fit, contrast=c(0,-1,1))

#ordering for ascendent adjusted p value (BH correction) p value 
topTags(qlfLiB, n=10,adjust.method = "BH", sort.by = "PValue")

brain_liver <- rownames(as.data.frame(resultsliB)[as.data.frame(resultsliB )$logFC < -1 & as.data.frame(resultsliB )$FDR < 0.01 & as.data.frame(resultsliB)$logCPM > 0 ,])

brain_vs_LiLu <- intersect(brain_liver,brain_lung )

  brain_vs_LiLu <- brain_vs_LiLu[which(!startsWith(brain_vs_LiLu, s))]
}

#same code, different target, now i want to find genes over
#expressed in Liver
liver_brain <- rownames(as.data.frame(resultsliB)[as.data.frame(resultsliB )$logFC > 1 & as.data.frame(resultsliB )$FDR < 0.01 & as.data.frame(resultsliB)$logCPM > 0 ,])

liver_lung <- rownames(as.data.frame(resultsLuLi)[as.data.frame(resultsLuB)$logFC < -1 & as.data.frame(resultsLuB)$FDR < 0.01 & as.data.frame(resultsLuB)$logCPM > 0 ,])

Liver_vs_BLu <- intersect(liver_brain,liver_lung )

# We can then trim the obtained list to remove genes that start with LOC, LINC, MIR, RPL and SNORD

starts = c('LOC', 'LINC', 'MIR', 'SNORD', 'RPL')

for(s in starts) {
  Liver_vs_BLu <- Liver_vs_BLu[which(!startsWith(Liver_vs_BLu, s))]
} 

DF_Li<-as.matrix(Liver_vs_BLu)

DF_Li<-data.frame(Liver_vs_BLu)
write.table(DF_Li, "genes_Li5.txt")
# same thing for lung 

lung_brain <- rownames(as.data.frame(resultsLuB)[as.data.frame(resultsLuB )$logFC > 1 & as.data.frame(resultsLuB )$FDR < 0.01 & as.data.frame(resultsLuB)$logCPM > 0 ,])

lung_liver <- rownames(as.data.frame(resultsLuLi)[as.data.frame(resultsLuLi)$logFC >1 & as.data.frame(resultsLuLi)$FDR < 0.01 & as.data.frame(resultsLuLi)$logCPM > 0 ,])

Lung_vs_BLi <- intersect(lung_brain,lung_liver )

# We can then trim the obtained list to remove genes that start with LOC, LINC, MIR, RPL and SNORD

starts = c('LOC', 'LINC', 'MIR', 'SNORD', 'RPL')

for(s in starts) {
  Lung_vs_BLi<- Lung_vs_BLi[which(!startsWith(Lung_vs_BLi, s))]
} 
length(Lung_vs_BLi)

DF_Lu<-as.matrix(Lung_vs_BLi)

## [1] 7793
df_br=data.frame(TPM=assays(rse_brain)$TPM[7793,],group="Brain")
df_li=data.frame(TPM=assays(rse_liver)$TPM[7793,],group="Liver")
df_lu=data.frame(TPM=assays(rse_lung)$TPM[7793,],group="Lung")
data_A1CF=rbind(df_br,df_li,df_lu) 

boxplot(assays(rse_brain)$TPM[7793,],assays(rse_liver)$TPM[7793,], assays(rse_lung)$TPM[7793,], outline=F 
        , main="TPM boxplot for GPR37L1 comparison",
        ylab="TPM", xlab="Sample", names=c("Brain","Liver","Lung"), col = c("#009999") )

#non parametric test made by kruskal- Wallis test 
#an extension of the  Wilcox test

res_kruskal=data_A1CF %>% kruskal_test(TPM ~ group)

pwc2=data_A1CF %>% wilcox_test(TPM ~ group, p.adjust.method = "BH")
pwc = pwc2 %>% add_xy_position(x = "group") #Auto-compute p-value label positions

ggboxplot(data_A1CF, x = "group", y = "TPM",outlier.shape = NA,width = 0.5,title="Expression of GPR37L1 gene",palette = "Blues"  ) +
  
  labs(subtitle = get_test_label(res_kruskal, detailed = TRUE),caption = get_pwc_label(pwc))+
  ylab("TPM") + geom_boxplot(color=c("#009999"),notch = TRUE)   +
